'''Adam Hložek''' (born 25 July 2002) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

==Club career==

===Sparta Prague===
Hložek was 12 years old when transferred from his hometown club Ivančice to [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]] along with his older brother Daniel, who was 16 at the time.<ref>{{cite web|first=David|last=Čermák|title=Úkaz jménem Hložek. Proč sparťanský teenager boří ligové rekordy?|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/adam-hlozek-sparta-prvni-ligovy-gol.A190310_204756_fotbal_rou|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=11 March 2019|language=cs}}</ref>

Four years later, on 2 October 2018, he made his first team debut in a [[Czech Cup]] match against {{ill|Slavoj Polná|cs|TJ Slavoj TKZ Polná}} as a substitute, scoring the final goal in a 4–1 away win.<ref>{{cite web|title=Polná 1–4 Sparta: Pražané v poháru postupují, outsider ale vzdoroval|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-domaci-souteze-pohar-facr/346478/polna-sparta-1-4-prazane-v-poharu-postupuji-outsider-ale-vzdoroval.html|website=[[Blesk]]|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]|date=2 October 2018|access-date=26 January 2021|language=cs}}</ref> Hložek made his league debut for Sparta Prague on 10 November 2018 in a 3–1 victory against [[MFK Karviná|Karviná]] at the age of 16 years, three months and 16 days – becoming the youngest Sparta player to appear in a league match.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|title=Nový Lafata z vlastní líhně? Hložek má titul nejmladšího sparťana|url=https://www.sport.cz/fotbal/synot-liga/clanek/1043841-novy-lafata-z-vlastni-lihne-hlozek-ma-titul-nejmladsiho-spartana.html|website=Sport.cz|publisher=Borgis|date=23 November 2018 |access-date=2 June 2022|archive-date=15 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215224131/https://www.sport.cz/fotbal/synot-liga/clanek/1043841-novy-lafata-z-vlastni-lihne-hlozek-ma-titul-nejmladsiho-spartana.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fotbal.idnes.cz/fortuna-liga-sparta-praha-adam-hlozek-nejmladsi-spartan-v-historii-1d3-/fotbal.aspx?c=A181110_162434_fotbal_vp2|title=Za minutu přepsal historii. Hložek je nejmladším sparťanem v české lize|date=10 November 2018|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|access-date=15 December 2018|language=cs|archive-date=15 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215223139/https://fotbal.idnes.cz/fortuna-liga-sparta-praha-adam-hlozek-nejmladsi-spartan-v-historii-1d3-/fotbal.aspx?c=A181110_162434_fotbal_vp2|url-status=live}}</ref>

Hložek finished the [[2020–21 Czech First League]] as joint top scorer, alongside [[Jan Kuchta]] with 15 goals, despite missing four months of the season due to injury.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/sport/fotbal/fotbal-liga-34-kolo-vysledky-sparta-brno-slavia-budejovice-hlozek-kuchta-kral_2105291937_mov|title=Sparta na závěr sezony deklasovala Brno, Slavia porazila Budějovice. Hložek čtyřmi góly dotáhl Kuchtu|date=29 May 2021|website=[[Czech Radio]]|access-date=30 May 2021|language=cs|archive-date=29 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210529174115/https://www.irozhlas.cz/sport/fotbal/fotbal-liga-34-kolo-vysledky-sparta-brno-slavia-budejovice-hlozek-kuchta-kral_2105291937_mov|url-status=live}}</ref> On 30 May 2021, a day after scoring four first-half goals in a 6–1 away victory against [[FC Zbrojovka Brno|Zbrojovka Brno]], Hložek signed a new contract extension until 2024 with Sparta Prague. Hložek finished the 2020–21 league season with 15 goals and seven assists in 19 games.

===Bayer Leverkusen===
{{Citation style|1=section|reason=Replace some match reports in sub-sections with actual news sources.|date=June 2024}}
On 2 June 2022, Hložek joined Bayer Leverkusen in Germany, signing a five-year contract, and got the number 23 on his jersey.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sparta.cz/en/article/adam-hlozek-signs-a-new-contract-38060|title=Adam Hložek signs a new contract!|date=30 May 2021|website=AC Sparta Prague|access-date=30 May 2021|archive-date=30 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210530081612/https://sparta.cz/en/article/adam-hlozek-signs-a-new-contract-38060|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2022–23: Debut season====
On 30 July 2022, Hložek scored a powerful shot outside the box against [[Elversberg]] on his debut.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Adam Hlozek: Who is the Czech teenager joining Bayer Leverkusen? |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/who-is-adam-hlozek-bayer-leverkusen-next-ibrahimovic-czech-republic-20175 |access-date=24 May 2024 |website=[[Bundesliga]]}}</ref> On 22 October 2022, against [[VFL Wolfsburg]], he provided a critical assist to draw 2–2.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Leverkusen vs VfL Wolfsburg|url=https://www.foxsports.com/soccer/bundesliga-bayer-leverkusen-vs-vfl-wolfsburg-oct-22-2022-game-boxscore-102784|website=[[Fox Sports (United States)|Fox Sports]]|date=22 October 2022|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref> On 26 October, Hložek would provide a vital assist against [[Atlético Madrid]] to make it 2–2 in the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayer Leverkusen late show stuns Diego Simeone's Atletico Madrid |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-atletico-madrid-champions-league-live-team-news-match-stats-21232|website=Bundesliga|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref> He continued this good form against [[Union Berlin]], which he provided another assist and a backheel goal to make it a comfortable 5–0 victory for Leverkusen.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Bayer Leverkusen stun Union Berlin as Mousa Diaby nets twice in second-half spectacular|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-union-berlin-live-team-news-match-stats-alonso-hudson-odoi-21769|website=Bundesliga|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref> Couple matches after, Hložek had another strong performance against [[Borussia Monchengladbach]] where he provided two assists in a 3–2 win.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Leverkusen 3-2 Gladbach (23 Jan, 2023) Final Score|url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/match/_/gameId/638579/bayer-leverkusen-borussia-monchengladbach|website=[[ESPN]]|date=23 January 2023|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref> In March, Hložek would head in the winning goal against [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Leverkusen outlast Werder Bremen in five-goal|url=https://www.flashscore.com/news/werder-bremen-bayer-leverkusen-report-2023-03-12/2Dkb4rWI/|website=Flash Score|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref> On 20 April 2023, Hložek scored and provided a goal against [[Union Saint-Gilloise]] in the [[2022–23 Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] and help Leverkusen to reach the semi-finals.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Union Saint-Gilloise vs Leverkusen|url=https://www.foxsports.com/soccer/europa-league-union-saint-gilloise-vs-bayer-leverkusen-apr-20-2023-game-boxscore-117623|website=Fox Sports|date=20 April 2023|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref> On 23 April 2023, Hložek scored to earn a 2–0 victory over [[RB Leipzig]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Leverkusen 2-0 RB Leipzig (23 Apr, 2023) Final Score|url=https://www.espn.in/football/match/_/gameId/638690/rb-leipzig-bayer-leverkusen|website=ESPN|date=23 April 2023|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref>

====2023–24 season====
In the first match of the season, Hložek scored twice and provided an assist off the bench during a 8–0 victory against Teutonia 05 in the [[DFB-Pokal]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Leverkusen 8-0 Teutonia|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/671658/bayer-leverkusen-teutonia-ottensen|website=ESPN|date=12 August 2023|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref> He scored again against [[SV Sandhausen]] in the next round.<ref>{{Cite web|title=5-2 in Sandhausen {{!}} Werkself through to Round of 16|url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/dfb-pokal/5-2-in-sandhausen-werkself-through-to-round-of-16|website=Bayer 04 Leverkusen|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref> On 9 February 2023, Hložek scored almost immediately off the bench in a 5–1 victory against [[SV Darmstadt 98]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Leverkusen 5-1 Darmstadt|url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/match/_/gameId/677603/sv-darmstadt-98-bayer-leverkusen|website=ESPN|date=2 September 2023|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref> On 5 October, Hložek provided an assist against [[Molde FK]] in the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Bayer Leverkusen vs. Molde|url=https://www.scorebar.com/live/1691-3739/molde-bayer-leverkusen|website=Scorebar|access-date=27 June 2024}}</ref> He scored a double goal against the Norwegian football club during the second leg which ended in a 5–1 victory for Leverkusen.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Bayer Leverkusen 5–1 Molde FK {{!}} UEFA Europa League 2023|url=https://forzafootball.com/match/1216628061|website=Forza Football|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref>

On 17 March 2024, Hložek scored an important goal in a 3–2 victory against [[SC Freiburg]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Desmond|last=Kane|title=SC Freiburg 2-3 Bayer Leverkusen: Xabi Alonso's Side Restore 10-point Advantage Over Bayern Munich with Win|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/bundesliga/2022-2023/sc-freiburg-2-3-bayer-leverkusen-xabi-alonsos-side-restore-10-point-advantage-over-bayern-munich-wit_sto10062699/story.shtml|website=Eurosport|date=17 March 2024|access-date=27 June 2024}}</ref> After returning from an ankle injury which had him ruled out for a month, he provided a [[Hattrick (football)|hattrick]] of assists against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in a 5–1 victory on 5 May 2024 and was awarded [[man of the match]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Four Things We Learnt from Bayer Leverkusen's win at Eintracht Frankfurt|url=https://www.vavel.com/en/international-football/2024/05/05/germany-bundesliga/1181661-four-things-we-learnt-from-bayer-leverkusens-win-at-eintracht-frankfurt.html|website=Vavel|date=5 May 2024|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref> Hložek played in the [[2024 UEFA Europa League final|2023–24 UEFA Europa League final]] with a shot outside the box in the last 20 minutes, but could not score and Leverkusen lost their 51-game unbeaten streak after losing 3–0 to [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=UEL Final {{!}} Atalanta 3-0 Bayer Leverkusen: Magnificent Lookman historic hat-trick|url=https://football-italia.net/uel-final-atalanta-3-0-bayer-leverkusen/|website=Football Italia|date=22 May 2024|access-date=24 May 2024}}</ref>

===TSG Hoffenheim===
On 17 August 2024, Hložek signed a multi-year contract with [[Bundesliga]] club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=TSG Hoffenheim verpflichtet Adam Hlozek|url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/aktuelles/news/2024/08/tsg-hoffenheim-verpflichtet-adam-hlozek|website=[[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim]]|date=17 August 2024|access-date=17 August 2024|language=de}}</ref> On matchday two in the Bundesliga, Hložek assisted [[Andrej Kramarić]] in a 3–1 loss against Frankfurt.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://en.as.com/resultados/futbol/alemania/2023_2024/directo/regular_a_8_443654/ | title=Hoffenheim 1-3 Eintracht Fr.: Results, summary and goals | date=23 October 2023 }}</ref> Hložek missed out on the next two games due to thigh problems but right after he scored his first goal for the club on 21 September 2024, against [[Werder Bremen]] in a 4–3 loss.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cq8x5k48jndt?page=7 | title=Hoffenheim vs Werder Bremen: Bundesliga }}</ref> On 3 October, Hložek scored his first brace for the club in a 2–0 win over [[Dynamo Kyiv]] in the Europa League.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/en/news/overview/2024/10/hlozek-bags-brace-as-tsg-beat-dynamo | title=Hložek bags brace as TSG beat Dynamo }}</ref> After a tremendous break with the national team, Hložek continued that momentum against [[RB Leipzig]] and scored another brace in another 4–3 win.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/hoffenheim-rb-leipzig-match-report-highlights-matchday-11-hlozek-bischof-29812 | title=Hoffenheim mount dramatic comeback late on to stun RB Leipzig in seven-goal thriller }}</ref>

On 18 January 2025, Hložek scored a brace against [[Holstein Kiel]] in a 3–1 win.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/holstein-kiel-hoffenheim-match-report-highlights-matchday-18-30519 | title=Adam Hložek propels Hoffenheim to crucial victory over Holstein Kiel }}</ref> On 27 January, Hložek assisted [[Gift Orban]] and scored a goal in the 96th minute to secure a 2–2 draw against Frankfurt.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://apnews.com/article/frankfurt-hoffenheim-pauli-union-berlin-bundesliga-0c1b07b4953eed1d0a82e0638e90511e | title=Hoffenheim's Hlozek scores late to end Frankfurt's winning run in 1st game since Marmoush left | website=[[Associated Press News]] | date=26 January 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://au.sports.yahoo.com/hoffenheims-hlozek-scores-end-frankfurt-165141957.html?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmluZy5jb20v&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAFQPKesHKHxf8ss3R5jRTjOF8KX1kvLMe0w_t7sOIW4DH7UNFgb7oFeIXRGAbrqJs5OfT3WR9HyXQjzUUfB5fqtLm4jOux1dr0qa1B5_QEacXlJYMW3crCz_rItk7M1gJtfmQSzETvN2HECD--B7HWtRZf3dptiaUY4sA0oHc3Yk | title=Hoffenheim's Hlozek scores late to end Frankfurt's winning run in 1st game since Marmoush left | date=26 January 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Dimitris Nikolaou & Adam Hložek, U21 CZE-GRE 2019-10-10 (cropped).jpg|thumb|180px|Hložek with the [[Czech Republic national under-21 football team|Czech Republic U21]] in 2019]]
On 4 September 2020, Hložek debuted for the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech senior squad]] in a [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League B|UEFA Nations League]] match against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Jiří|last=Čihák|title=Zápis do historie. Hložek je nejmladším reprezentantem, při debutu trefil tyč|trans-title=Writing in history: Hložek is the youngest representative. He hit the post on his debut|url=https://www.lidovky.cz/sport/fotbal/zapis-do-historie-hlozek-je-nejmladsim-reprezentantem-pri-debutu-trefil-tyc.A200904_232546_ln-sport-fotbal_janl|url-status=dead|date=5 September 2020|website=[[Lidové noviny]]|language=cs|access-date=23 April 2024|archive-date=23 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240423102538/https://www.lidovky.cz/sport/fotbal/zapis-do-historie-hlozek-je-nejmladsim-reprezentantem-pri-debutu-trefil-tyc.A200904_232546_ln-sport-fotbal_janl}}</ref>

In May 2021, Hložek was called up by the Czech Republic for the rescheduled [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Euro 2020 squads: France, Spain, Germany & every official tournament panel list|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/euro-2020-squads/120zvuewm6geh11kkoe59otixw#1jbrvwiz26wc51frt2pec3cpsc|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=30 May 2021}}</ref> He scored his first international goal in October 2021 in the 2–0 [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group E|World Cup qualification]] victory against [[Belarus national football team|Belarus]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Czechs defeat Belarus 2–0 in World Cup qualifier, make playoffs|url=https://english.radio.cz/czechs-defeat-belarus-20-world-cup-qualifier-make-playoffs-8730978|website=[[Radio Prague]]|date=12 October 2021}}</ref>

